    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.5241/78</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of War</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose copies of
                    correspondence exchanged between this Department and the British Embassy at this
                    Capital, on the subject of the applicability to Porto Rico of the <pb
                        facs="0361" n="285" xml:id="pg_285"/> Treaty of March 2, 1899, between the
                    United States and Great Britain, concerning the tenure and disposition of real
                    and personal property.</p>
                <p>The Department will be glad to receive an expression of your views in the matter,
                    as well as of those of the Governor of Porto Rico.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
